DOCUMENT();
############################################################ # Load Macros ############################################################ loadMacros( "PGstandard.pl", "PGML.pl", "AnswerFormatHelp.pl", "PCCmacros.pl", "contextCurrency.pl", "parserLinearRelation.pl", "randomPerson.pl", "PGcourse.pl", ); COMMENT('Authored in PreTeXt');
############################################################ # Header ############################################################ TEXT(beginproblem());
############################################################ # PG Setup Code ############################################################ $name = randomPerson(); $initial = random(800,1000,20); Context("Currency")->flags->set(trimTrailingZeros => 1); $start = Currency($initial); $rate = random(200,250,5); $speed = Currency($rate); $final = random(80,100,10); $end = Currency($final); Context("LinearRelation")->variables->are(t => 'Real'); $equation = LinearRelation("$initial - $rate t = $final");
############################################################ # Body ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML Read the scenario. Then write a complete sentence that defines a variable to use. Lastly, write an equation to model the scenario. There is no need to solve the equation.
At a recent trip to the casino, [$name] brought [`[$start]`] in cash. [$name->Subject] [$name->verb('know')] [$name->subject] [$name->verb('need')] to hold on to [`[$end]`] in reserve to pay for dinner later. Unfortunately [$name] had rough luck and was losing money at the slot machines at an average rate of [`[$speed]`] per hour. How long was [$name] gambling before [$name->subject] had to stop? Write an equation to model this scenario. There is no need to solve it.
[@KeyboardInstructions('Use [|t|]* as the variable.')@]**
[_]{$equation}{20}
END_PGML
